{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017XRBKQoxZR772p1etsboYg","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Closecall Program Deployment Setup - Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. **Program Configuration (Anchor.toml)**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/Anchor.toml`\n\n- **Program ID**: `8TXq2XyHsk5AAMkoyk5QtG25xyyY7rTMHXrJRHRwjUpA` (same on localnet and devnet)\n- **Anchor version**: 0.32.1\n- **Cluster**: Configured as `Localnet` in provider (line 25), but deploy script switches to devnet\n- **Deploy wallet**: `~/.config/solana/id.json`\n\n### 2. **.env.devnet Configuration**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/.env.devnet` (root level)\n\n- **SOLANA_DEPLOYER_KEY**: Contains a deterministic keypair (byte array) for repeatable deploys\n- **Deployer address**: `AXjQcFUUs2rs6tWqN7ykNWtXesjaGCu3JoGvU2STNUP6`\n- Note: No dedicated `.env.devnet` at `sources/rng-utopia/` level (file does not exist)\n\n### 3. **Program Structure**\n\n**Workspace**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/`\n\n- **Root Cargo.toml workspace members**: Includes `programs/closecall` as a member\n- **Program crate location**: `solana/programs/closecall/`\n- **Crate dependencies**: \n  - `anchor-lang` (workspace = 0.32.1)\n  - `rng-shared` (workspace library)\n- **Library type**: Both cdylib (on-chain) and lib (off-chain testing)\n\n**Program entry point**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/closecall/src/lib.rs`\n- `declare_id!(\"8TXq2XyHsk5AAMkoyk5QtG25xyyY7rTMHXrJRHRwjUpA\")`\n\n### 4. **Closecall IDL & Instruction Set**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/closecall.ts`\n\n**Program ID in IDL**: `8TXq2XyHsk5AAMkoyk5QtG25xyyY7rTMHXrJRHRwjUpA`\n\n**Six public instructions**:\n1. `initialize_config` — Setup global config (treasury, Pyth feed ID, betting window, max entries per side)\n2. `create_round` — Server creates a new round (captures Pyth open price)\n3. `place_bet` — Player bets on either green (bull, side=0) or red (bear, side=1)\n4. `settle_round` — Settlement caller resolves outcome (captures Pyth close price, distributes payouts)\n5. `timeout_refund` — Permissionless refund after deadline expires\n6. `force_close` — Admin force-close a round (administrative recovery)\n\n**Two main accounts**:\n- `CloseCallConfig` (PDA seeds: `[\"closecall_config\"]`) — Global config, 1 per program\n- `CloseCallRound` (PDA seeds: `[\"cc_round\", round_id (8-byte)]`) — Per-round state\n\n### 5. **Pyth Integration**\n\n**Feed ID (Mainnet/Devnet)**: BTC/USD\n- **Hex**: `0xe62df6c8b4a85fe1a67db44dc12de5db330f7ac66b72dc658afedf0f4a415b43`\n- **As 32-byte array** (from test): `e62df6c8b4a85fe1a67db44dc12de5db` + `330f7ac66b72dc658afedf0f4a415b43`\n\n**Source file**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/price-feeds/src/types.ts`\n\n**Pyth parser module**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/closecall/src/pyth.rs`\n- Parses `PriceUpdateV2` account format (Pyth's on-chain price structure)\n- Validates feed ID matches config\n- Checks price staleness (max age configurable)\n\n**Backend Pyth config**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/config.ts`\n- `pythBtcUsdAccount`: Defaults to `4cSM2e6rvbGQUFiJbqytoVMi5GgghSMr8LwVrT9VPSPo` (can be overridden via env)\n\n### 6. **InitializeConfig Instruction Details**\n\n**Handler**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/solana/programs/closecall/src/instructions/initialize_config.rs`\n\n**Required parameters**:\n```rust\npub fn initialize_config(\n    ctx: Context<InitializeConfig>,\n    treasury: Pubkey,                    // Fee destination\n    pyth_feed_id: [u8; 32],             // BTC/USD feed ID\n    betting_window_secs: u32,           // Duration (default 30)\n    max_entries_per_side: u8,           // Cap per side (default 32)\n) -> Result<()>\n```\n\n**Config account fields**:\n- `authority`: Signer (admin)\n- `treasury`: Fee destination wallet\n- `pyth_feed_id`: 32-byte Pyth feed ID\n- `betting_window_secs`: Betting duration (u32)\n- `max_entries_per_side`: Entry cap (u8)\n- `paused`: Boolean (initialized to false)\n- `bump`: PDA bump seed\n\n### 7. **Deployment & Test Pattern**\n\n**Deploy script**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/scripts/deploy-devnet.sh`\n\n- Deploys via `anchor build -- --no-default-features` (VRF enabled, no mock)\n- **Does NOT currently deploy closecall** — only coinflip, platform, and lordofrngs (lines 76-78)\n- Calls `scripts/init-devnet-config.ts` for post-deploy initialization\n\n**Init script**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/solana/scripts/init-devnet-config.ts`\n\n- Loads wallet from `~/.config/solana/id.json`\n- Connects to Solana devnet (`https://api.devnet.solana.com`)\n- **Currently initializes**: platform, coinflip, lordofrngs\n- **Does NOT currently initialize closecall** (would need to add closecall IDL loading + init call)\n- Treats treasury = deployer wallet for devnet\n\n### 8. **Game-Engine Constants**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/closecall.ts`\n\n- Exports `CLOSECALL_PROGRAM_ID` derived from IDL address\n- Exports PDA derivation functions:\n  - `getCloseCallRoundPda(roundId)` — Seeds: `[\"cc_round\", roundId]`\n  - `getCloseCallConfigPda()` — Seeds: `[\"closecall_config\"]`\n\n### 9. **Test Coverage**\n\n**Bankrun test file**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/solana/tests/closecall.ts`\n\n- Uses `anchor-bankrun` for local testing\n- Defines constants:\n  - MIN_WAGER: 1,000,000 lamports (0.001 SOL)\n  - BETTING_WINDOW_SECS: 30\n  - MAX_ENTRIES_PER_SIDE: 32\n  - TOTAL_FEE_BPS: 300 (3%)\n  - PYTH_BTC_USD_FEED_ID: Same as production\n- Implements mock Pyth `PriceUpdateV2` account builder for testing\n\n### 10. **Key Gotchas & Observations**\n\n1. **Deploy script incomplete**: `deploy-devnet.sh` does NOT print closecall program ID or initialize it. Lines 76-78 only show coinflip, platform, lordofrngs.\n\n2. **Init script incomplete**: `init-devnet-config.ts` does NOT load closecall IDL or call `initialize_config`.\n\n3. **Pyth price account required**: Both `create_round` and `settle_round` require a valid Pyth `PriceUpdateV2` account for the BTC/USD feed as an input account.\n\n4. **PDA seeds are fixed**: All round PDAs use `[\"cc_round\", round_id]` where `round_id` is an 8-byte backend-generated identifier.\n\n5. **State size**: CloseCallRound is dynamically sized (vec of entries), with a max of 32 entries per side (72 bytes fixed + ~80 bytes per entry = ~3KB per fully populated round).\n\n6. **Pyth account parsing**: Custom deserialization in `pyth.rs` to avoid SDK version conflicts; relies on `PriceUpdateV2` account format with 8-byte discriminator + Borsh-serialized inner struct.\n\n---\n\n**Summary**: Closecall is fully implemented in the Anchor workspace with IDL, program ID locked in `Anchor.toml`, and state structures defined. However, **deployment to devnet requires updating**:\n1. Add closecall to `deploy-devnet.sh` output and keypair extraction\n2. Add closecall IDL loading and `initialize_config` call to `init-devnet-config.ts`\n3. Provide backend config for `pythBtcUsdAccount` (on-chain Pyth PriceUpdateV2 account address)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0b4e31fa20a4d564 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 59972\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 96458</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dfed5053-bbec-4b81-a37f-49b6882e5396","uuid":"1525d318-b7fd-4665-abab-3339589c0d6c","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the closecall program deployment setup. Find and read:\n\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/solana/Anchor.toml` — look for closecall program ID, cluster config, deploy wallet path\n2. `.env.devnet` files — check both `sources/rng-utopia/.env.devnet` and root `.env.devnet` for existing CLOSECA