{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JD8gvXrm1bC5zDZKBVWEuD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The price became stale again by the time the script ran (building the tx, sending it). The Pyth devnet price updates are sporadic. Let me try a different approach — modify the script to poll for fresh price and then immediately submit, all in the same execution flow.\n\nActually, let me be smarter about this. I'll have the script check the price age first, wait for it to be fresh, and then immediately build and send the transaction. The key issue is that between the price check and the tx submission, the price ages.\n\nActually, the issue is more fundamental: on devnet, Pyth prices update only every few minutes. The 60-second staleness window in the program is designed for mainnet where prices update every second. On devnet, the update frequency is much lower.\n\n\nSo the real problem isn't my implementation — the program is working correctly, all my tests pass, and the config is set up right. The PriceTooStale error is actually the program doing its job. The bottleneck is just that devnet's Pyth price feed updates too infrequently to work with my staleness threshold.\n\nI should tighten up the verification script to poll for a fresh price and submit the transaction immediately without any rebuilding in between, or pre-construct the transaction and only fire it off once the price data is current.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1135,"cache_read_input_tokens":85813,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1135},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dfed5053-bbec-4b81-a37f-49b6882e5396","uuid":"eccec9a1-ece0-4362-a395-d580aee37af2"}
